Installing Curo
===========================================================================

Reference information:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following dependencies, setup and configuration instructions are to
be considered suggestions, not rules.  It is quite possible to use for
example SQLite as database engine instead of MySQL, &c.

Dependencies
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Django-1.3.1
  - <http://www.djangoproject.com/download/>

- mysql and mysql-server
  - <http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/>

- MySQL-python
  - <http://sourceforge.net/projects/mysql-python/>

- Tastypie
  - <https://github.com/toastdriven/django-tastypie>
  - <http://django-tastypie.readthedocs.org/en/latest/tutorial.html#installation>

Setup
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Create a project:

    $ git clone https://github.com/reggna/Curo.git

Create a database and a user with access to it. Modify the settings.py file
to use the correct database settings. SQLite is setup to work out-of-the-box.

Sync the models to the database:

    $ python manage.py syncdb
    
TODO: Add sensible fixture

Start the server:

    $ python manage.py runserver

